WEBVTT

00:01.334 --> 00:04.036
(funky disco plays)
♪My name is Cleveland Brown

00:04.038 --> 00:06.438
♪And I am proud to be

00:06.440 --> 00:08.307
♪Right back in my hometown

00:08.309 --> 00:11.477
♪With my new family

00:11.479 --> 00:13.445
♪There's old friends
and new friends ♪

00:13.447 --> 00:15.781
♪And even a bear

00:15.783 --> 00:18.017
♪Through good times
and bad times ♪

00:18.019 --> 00:19.385
♪It's true love we share

00:19.387 --> 00:21.720
♪And so I found a place

00:21.722 --> 00:24.289
♪Where everyone will know

00:24.291 --> 00:26.392
♪My happy mustached face

00:26.394 --> 00:28.193
♪This is <i>The Cleveland Show.♪</i>

00:28.195 --> 00:30.462
(chuckles)

00:33.967 --> 00:36.668
And then to accelerate the fire,
you can use grease,

00:36.670 --> 00:38.504
which you might find
in ground beef,

00:38.506 --> 00:40.973
which you might find
in my pocket.

00:40.975 --> 00:42.908
(audience gasps)

00:44.677 --> 00:46.578
Thank you,
Cleveland, Jr.

00:46.580 --> 00:48.647
I'll have to send
you to my ex-wife's house.

00:48.649 --> 00:50.382
Just kidding.
Never had sex.

00:50.384 --> 00:52.084
Clean Team, advance.

01:03.830 --> 01:05.230
Boys doing chores.

01:05.232 --> 01:07.032
Mm.

01:07.034 --> 01:08.233
And looking right
in their crisp uniforms.

01:08.235 --> 01:10.769
Yep, everyone
looks good in khaki.

01:10.771 --> 01:13.338
Especially
lady zookeepers.

01:13.340 --> 01:14.339
Mm.

01:14.341 --> 01:15.741
Excuse me, ma'am.

01:15.743 --> 01:17.709
Can I freshen up
your Dixie cup of trail mix?

01:17.711 --> 01:18.844
Thank you.

01:18.846 --> 01:20.612
No yellow raisins.

01:20.614 --> 01:23.782
All these Scouts
are so well-behaved and polite.

01:23.784 --> 01:25.217
Ugh.

01:25.219 --> 01:26.351
How about you,
young man?

01:26.353 --> 01:27.920
A little trail mix?

01:27.922 --> 01:30.389
Gorp... aka "Good Old
Raisins and Peanuts"?

01:30.391 --> 01:31.557
Uh, no.

01:31.559 --> 01:33.692
I prefer Gofu, as in Go F--

01:33.694 --> 01:35.227
Rallo!

01:35.229 --> 01:37.429
You know, you could learn
a thing or two from these boys.

01:37.431 --> 01:39.031
Yeah, like how
to be a kiss-ass.

01:39.033 --> 01:39.965
Dork.

01:39.967 --> 01:41.233
Rallo!

01:41.235 --> 01:42.734
You could
use some of that.

01:42.736 --> 01:44.403
Give you
a better attitude.

01:44.405 --> 01:46.805
The world's got
enough critics.

01:46.807 --> 01:48.640
Little bastard left
a yellow raisin in here.

01:48.642 --> 01:50.409
Attention Freedom Scouts,

01:50.411 --> 01:52.478
Freedom Scout families--

01:52.480 --> 01:54.079
it's time for the raffle.

01:54.081 --> 01:58.283
First up, our third prize,
a massage from a man.

01:58.285 --> 02:01.954
Ticket number... 412.

02:01.956 --> 02:04.156
Number 412.

02:04.158 --> 02:06.658
No one wants
a massage from a man?

02:09.496 --> 02:12.664
Second prize, a walk-on
on <i>The Cleveland Show.</i>

02:12.666 --> 02:14.399
Number 713.

02:16.603 --> 02:17.903
Hi, Gene Oshman.

02:17.905 --> 02:19.071
Big fan, Cleveland.

02:19.073 --> 02:20.973
Mm-hmm.

02:20.975 --> 02:23.609
First prize,
a complimentary weekend

02:23.611 --> 02:26.745
at Stoolbend's new romantic
luxury hotel,

02:26.747 --> 02:29.648
The Bendit Inn,
and a massage from a man.

02:29.650 --> 02:32.017
Number 232.

02:32.019 --> 02:33.619
That's me!

02:33.621 --> 02:35.254
Thank God we can be
away from our children.

02:35.256 --> 02:36.955
Hooray.

02:36.957 --> 02:39.091
Congratsies!

02:39.093 --> 02:40.626
The winner is Donna Tubbs,

02:40.628 --> 02:42.427
mother of one of our Scouts.

02:42.429 --> 02:45.364
Correction:
two of your Scouts.

02:45.366 --> 02:48.367
My son Rallo will be at
your initiation ceremony

02:48.369 --> 02:51.770
on Sunday, so he, too,
can become a Freedom Scout.

02:51.772 --> 02:53.839
What?
How old is he?

02:53.841 --> 02:55.474
Five.

02:55.476 --> 02:57.209
Then he shall be
a Freedom Squirt.

02:57.977 --> 02:59.378
Hi, Karen, hi, kids.

02:59.380 --> 03:01.346
Get your ass
out my shot.

03:05.185 --> 03:07.686
But Mama, I don't want to
join his stupid club.

03:07.688 --> 03:08.887
It's for squares.

03:08.889 --> 03:10.689
Or circles, in his case.

03:10.691 --> 03:12.024
You can do this, Rallo.

03:12.026 --> 03:13.559
All we got to do
is complete your

03:13.561 --> 03:15.561
Freedom Squirt
task checklist.

03:15.563 --> 03:17.062
Oh, is
that all, Junior?

03:17.064 --> 03:17.996
Is that all?

03:17.998 --> 03:19.331
You heard him.

03:19.333 --> 03:21.567
Now, I am going
to a fine hotel,

03:21.569 --> 03:23.969
and when I come home,
I'm gonna have two things:

03:23.971 --> 03:26.638
one, a new bathrobe,
and two,

03:26.640 --> 03:29.708
a polite, respectful
Freedom Squirt for a son.

03:29.710 --> 03:31.476
Or else, no more
dinosaur guys in the bath.

03:31.478 --> 03:32.477
Ever!

03:32.479 --> 03:33.478
Ugh.

03:33.480 --> 03:34.913
Just me and the soap?

03:34.915 --> 03:37.516
(shudders)
You're a monster.

03:37.518 --> 03:39.518
A monster on vacation.

03:39.520 --> 03:41.486
See ya!

03:41.488 --> 03:43.889
(quietly): Donna, I didn't
pack any pajama bottoms.

03:43.891 --> 03:46.158
Roberta's in charge!
Bye!

03:46.160 --> 03:47.993
We better get cracking
if we want to knock out

03:47.995 --> 03:49.661
eight tasks by tuck-in.

03:49.663 --> 03:50.996
I don't want
anything to do with

03:50.998 --> 03:52.431
your goody-goody
khaki cult.

03:52.433 --> 03:54.166
What?!
It's a sham.

03:54.168 --> 03:56.735
Kids being forced to do
"good things"

03:56.737 --> 03:59.404
to get badges
and a pat on the head.

03:59.406 --> 04:02.674
That is, as long as they pay
the initiation fee.

04:02.676 --> 04:04.876
I'm going to open
your heart, Rallo.

04:04.878 --> 04:08.080
And when I'm done,
you'll be a Freedom Squirt.

04:08.082 --> 04:09.181
You know what?

04:09.183 --> 04:10.616
I'm gonna
take the bottoms.

04:10.618 --> 04:13.352
I don't want Donna seeing
my pimply backside.

04:13.354 --> 04:15.120
It's embarrassing.

04:18.224 --> 04:21.693
Not gonna lie, nicest place
I've ever stayed by a lot.

04:21.695 --> 04:23.929
Two lamps.

04:23.931 --> 04:25.530
Honestly, I thought
it would be a little nicer.

04:25.532 --> 04:28.533
(truck beeping)

04:28.535 --> 04:30.369
Cool! Cars!

04:30.371 --> 04:31.737
Lightning McQueen.

04:31.739 --> 04:34.640
Hey, Mater,
you're my friend.

04:34.642 --> 04:37.776
Okay, now that I've
put you in the mood.

04:37.778 --> 04:39.878
Uh-uh!
Not in this room.

04:39.880 --> 04:42.214
Donna, no,
they'll hate us.

04:42.216 --> 04:44.816
Hello, this is
contest winner Donna Tubbs.

04:44.818 --> 04:47.552
We were really
hoping for a garden view.

04:47.554 --> 04:48.654
Please don't
spit in our bed.

04:48.656 --> 04:50.589
Oh, you'd
move us to a new room?

04:50.591 --> 04:52.924
Great! Thank you.

04:52.926 --> 04:55.360
That other room
better have two lamps.

04:56.262 --> 04:59.164
Four lamps?!

05:00.566 --> 05:03.135
Now this
is more like it.

05:03.137 --> 05:06.438
That room over
there has a terrace.

05:06.440 --> 05:08.340
I am so sorry
that one of our maids

05:08.342 --> 05:10.075
left a hair
dryer on in the sink.

05:10.077 --> 05:11.910
Well, I appreciate
that, but still,

05:11.912 --> 05:14.079
I was badly electrocuted.

05:14.081 --> 05:15.681
Look what
happened to her head.

05:15.683 --> 05:17.482
Oh, my God, you look horrible.

05:17.484 --> 05:19.318
Well!

05:19.320 --> 05:21.486
Rest assured, we have
upgraded you to a nicer room.

05:21.488 --> 05:23.155
Can you upgrade her?

05:23.157 --> 05:24.289
How am I supposed
to sleep with that?

05:24.291 --> 05:25.023
(laughing)

05:25.025 --> 05:26.692
Kidding.

05:26.694 --> 05:28.126
Please let
me have some later.

05:28.128 --> 05:29.728
We're at a hotel.

05:34.534 --> 05:36.201
It worked!

05:36.203 --> 05:38.437
And this is the
best room we've had.

05:38.439 --> 05:40.439
So far.

05:44.644 --> 05:46.712
Hi, we've got birds.

05:48.881 --> 05:50.515
All right, six more.

05:50.517 --> 05:53.051
Next up, "Citizenship."

05:53.053 --> 05:56.188
How about helping that
homeless gentleman over there?

05:56.190 --> 05:57.556
He ain't homeless.

05:57.558 --> 05:58.357
He just been at
the beach all day.

05:58.359 --> 06:00.359
Look at that tan.

06:00.361 --> 06:02.127
He's just trying
to scam us, Junior.

06:02.129 --> 06:04.196
Rallo, what's wrong
with you?

06:04.198 --> 06:06.131
I'm so sorry
about that, sir.

06:06.133 --> 06:07.566
Have a chocolate bar.

06:07.568 --> 06:09.267
Thanks, Black Santa.

06:12.638 --> 06:15.974
Wow, Junior, that's a lot of
chocolate, even for you.

06:15.976 --> 06:17.843
I bought 40 boxes of
these to support

06:17.845 --> 06:19.478
the Troubled Youth
Orchestra of Stoolbend.

06:19.480 --> 06:21.246
I'm singlehandedly

06:21.248 --> 06:23.081
sending them to perform
in Norfolk.

06:23.083 --> 06:24.216
Oh, okay.

06:24.218 --> 06:27.085
Some "troubled youths"
sold you these?

06:27.087 --> 06:29.321
Yeah.
And I'm sure they gave you

06:29.323 --> 06:32.524
a great deal
on these 50-cent candy bars.

06:32.526 --> 06:34.659
(chuckling):
Oh, child...

06:34.661 --> 06:36.595
these are not
50-cent candy bars.

06:36.597 --> 06:38.563
They're five-dollar
candy bars.

06:38.565 --> 06:40.432
I see.

06:40.434 --> 06:43.101
And if I were inclined to
support their organization,

06:43.103 --> 06:45.737
where might I acquire
such candy bars?

06:49.776 --> 06:51.243
Send the Troubled
Youth Orchestra of Stoolbend

06:51.245 --> 06:52.844
to the
Norfolk Music Festival.

06:52.846 --> 06:54.546
One year from tonight.

06:54.548 --> 06:56.515
So, you're the kids who
have been taking advantage

06:56.517 --> 06:58.517
of my step-brother,
making him believe

06:58.519 --> 07:01.086
you're an orchestra
gonna go play in Norfolk?

07:01.088 --> 07:02.220
What?!

07:02.222 --> 07:03.688
We're legit.

07:03.690 --> 07:05.524
We got a concert
one year from tonight.

07:05.526 --> 07:06.525
Name an instrument.

07:06.527 --> 07:08.560
Uh... trumpullet?

07:08.562 --> 07:10.128
Lucky guess.

07:10.130 --> 07:11.096
What you want?

07:11.098 --> 07:12.397
What do I want?!

07:12.399 --> 07:14.199
You messed
with my step-kin!

07:14.201 --> 07:15.634
What do you
think I want?

07:15.636 --> 07:17.202
I want in.

07:17.204 --> 07:19.604
50/50 split
on the first six boxes I sell,

07:19.606 --> 07:21.273
60/40 after that.

07:21.275 --> 07:23.742
And at 20 boxes, I get points
on the back end

07:23.744 --> 07:25.644
retroactive to right now.

07:25.646 --> 07:27.579
Kid knows his stuff.

07:27.581 --> 07:30.482
Let's see your begging face.

07:30.484 --> 07:32.651
"Pweez" buy my candy.

07:32.653 --> 07:35.287
I'm "hon-gwy."

07:35.289 --> 07:36.455
I'll take two.

07:36.457 --> 07:37.489
No, Puffs.

07:37.491 --> 07:38.690
You in.

07:40.159 --> 07:42.227
Stay tuned, "Ame-wica."

07:42.229 --> 07:44.863
We need the "watings."

07:51.471 --> 07:53.138
Oh, gee,
this tub was filled

07:53.140 --> 07:54.606
with candy bars
this morning.

07:54.608 --> 07:55.807
But they're gone.

07:55.809 --> 07:57.476
What's in there now?

07:57.478 --> 07:59.077
Boom!

07:59.079 --> 08:01.746
♪Rallo's in a tub of money!

08:01.748 --> 08:02.781
(high-pitched):
♪Money.

08:02.783 --> 08:04.483
(both laughing)

08:04.485 --> 08:06.751
Wow, Rallo!
All that cash is for the

08:06.753 --> 08:08.286
Troubled Youth Orchestra?

08:08.288 --> 08:09.788
(evil laughter)

08:09.790 --> 08:11.756
(sarcastically):
Yeah, right.

08:11.758 --> 08:14.359
I mean, uh... yeah, right.

08:14.361 --> 08:17.162
Always happy to keep
the youths in trumpullets.

08:17.164 --> 08:19.264
I'm so proud of
you, Rallo.

08:19.266 --> 08:22.133
You were so cynical,
but I touched you.

08:22.135 --> 08:23.768
And if I
could touch you,

08:23.770 --> 08:26.004
think of how many
other boys I could touch.

08:26.006 --> 08:27.939
(Junior whistling happily)

08:27.941 --> 08:28.473
(chuckling)

08:32.211 --> 08:35.380
Mm, best vacation
we've ever had.

08:35.382 --> 08:36.648
With all the

08:36.650 --> 08:37.949
"ammeminenities."

08:37.951 --> 08:39.484
(sighs)

08:39.486 --> 08:42.020
Glad we upgraded
to the Presidential Suite.

08:42.022 --> 08:44.289
How could they expect us
to stay in a room

08:44.291 --> 08:47.225
where a "dog" had scooted
across the carpet?

08:47.227 --> 08:48.460
(both laughing)

08:50.830 --> 08:53.064
(siren wailing
in distance)

08:54.834 --> 08:56.468
We're here.

08:56.470 --> 08:59.237
Time for your surprise
for all your hard work.

08:59.239 --> 09:00.639
This looks like Norfolk.

09:00.641 --> 09:01.673
Are we in Norfolk?

09:01.675 --> 09:03.174
Yeah.

09:03.176 --> 09:05.210
For the big Troubled
Youth Orchestra concert.

09:05.212 --> 09:06.878
What?!

09:06.880 --> 09:08.980
Last year, when I bought
my very first candy bar,

09:08.982 --> 09:13.852
they said, "See our big concert,
one year from tonight."

09:13.854 --> 09:16.755
Look, Junior, I think you
might be a bit disappointed.

09:16.757 --> 09:18.256
How could I be?

09:18.258 --> 09:20.191
Just to see the
smile on your face

09:20.193 --> 09:22.861
as you listen to these
needy kids that we've helped.

09:22.863 --> 09:25.397
That will be
music to my eyes.

09:25.399 --> 09:27.165
Ooh, here's the address.

09:27.167 --> 09:30.435
Say, Jim, you standing
in my moon shadow.

09:30.437 --> 09:32.571
Uh, is this where the Troubled
Youth Orchestra is performing?

09:32.573 --> 09:33.838
Oh, yeah, yeah.

09:33.840 --> 09:34.573
They're just tuning up.

09:34.575 --> 09:36.074
Listen.

09:36.076 --> 09:38.944
(farting)

09:38.946 --> 09:42.747
Rallo, there is
no orchestra, is there?

09:42.749 --> 09:44.382
No, big guy.

09:44.384 --> 09:45.951
And the money I've
been giving for candy bars,

09:45.953 --> 09:47.385
you and the rest of those guys

09:47.387 --> 09:49.187
have just been
keeping all of it?

09:49.189 --> 09:51.456
And making it rain at
Toys "R" Us.

09:54.026 --> 09:55.026
Huh.

09:55.028 --> 09:56.061
Good one, Rallo.

09:56.063 --> 09:57.195
You got me.

09:57.197 --> 09:59.798
The old Troubled Youth
Orchestra Trick.

09:59.800 --> 10:02.801
(chuckling): Welp,
better get home to bed.

10:02.803 --> 10:04.869
Got that initiation
in the morning.

10:04.871 --> 10:05.937
Hm.

10:05.939 --> 10:08.039
Fatso's rolling with it.

10:08.041 --> 10:10.175
And I best get my ass
out of this neighborhood.

10:13.713 --> 10:14.713
Checking out?

10:14.715 --> 10:16.147
How was your stay?

10:16.149 --> 10:18.917
Oh, it was very
relaxing, thanks.

10:18.919 --> 10:21.086
Even my husband's
hair is relaxed.

10:21.088 --> 10:22.621
Hi.

10:22.623 --> 10:25.223
That's what
we like to hear.

10:25.225 --> 10:28.460
Okay, your balance is
$3,217.00.

10:28.462 --> 10:30.061
Come again?

10:30.063 --> 10:31.830
Oh, I think there's
a misunderstanding.

10:31.832 --> 10:34.065
See, we're contest winners.

10:34.067 --> 10:36.301
Right, so your room
was free, but you do have

10:36.303 --> 10:37.469
to pay for incidentals,

10:37.471 --> 10:39.270
including in-room dining,

10:39.272 --> 10:41.773
minibar, seven couples
massages, dry cleaning,

10:41.775 --> 10:43.808
midnight swim with the dolphins,

10:43.810 --> 10:46.244
as well as the 72-hour
porn pass you ordered.

10:46.246 --> 10:50.248
For the record, I only used
three minutes of it.

10:50.250 --> 10:53.118
Guess my eyes were
bigger than my hands.

10:53.120 --> 10:55.353
We don't have $3,200!

10:55.355 --> 10:56.821
Don't worry.
I got this.

10:56.823 --> 10:59.324
Birds! Uhp.

10:59.326 --> 11:01.593
Look, if you can't afford
to pay your bill,

11:01.595 --> 11:03.461
you're gonna have
to work it off.

11:03.463 --> 11:04.996
Standard sitcom policy.

11:06.999 --> 11:10.168
Really? This is really the
only uniform you got for me?

11:10.170 --> 11:13.805
Yep. Lots of beefy gals
come through this place.

11:13.807 --> 11:17.709
Now, I believe the toilet
in 416 is clogged.

11:17.711 --> 11:19.678
Lots of beefy guests, too.

11:19.680 --> 11:21.079
(both sigh)

11:23.549 --> 11:25.850
Hiya, a-roonie-yah!

11:25.852 --> 11:28.153
Hiya, a-scoonie-yah!

11:28.155 --> 11:33.324
Hiya, soota dada yo-yo
da-baba, yah!

11:33.326 --> 11:34.826
So you're sure
you're cool with me

11:34.828 --> 11:35.660
going through with this?

11:35.662 --> 11:37.295
So cool.

11:42.068 --> 11:44.402
And now to launch
our Pre-Squirts

11:44.404 --> 11:47.038
into full-fledged
Freedom Squirtdom,

11:47.040 --> 11:49.674
Chief Scout
Cleveland Brown, Jr.!

11:49.676 --> 11:52.877
(applause, mic feedback whines)

11:52.879 --> 11:55.547
Well, here they are,
Freedom Squirt badges--

11:55.549 --> 11:58.850
symbols of trust, honesty,
and integrity.

11:58.852 --> 12:01.186
In other words, total bullcrap!

12:01.188 --> 12:02.153
(all gasp)

12:02.155 --> 12:03.988
Hiya, what the...?!

12:03.990 --> 12:06.758
That's right, kids--
might as well tell you now:

12:06.760 --> 12:09.160
It's a soulless world
full of bad people

12:09.162 --> 12:10.895
who screw you at every turn.

12:10.897 --> 12:12.297
Scout's honor.

12:13.332 --> 12:14.899
I quit!

12:14.901 --> 12:16.401
(all gasp)

12:16.403 --> 12:17.769
(woman gasps,
audience murmuring)

12:18.404 --> 12:20.371
Junior, wait!

12:20.373 --> 12:21.740
Buy some chocolates
for the road?

12:21.742 --> 12:23.241
Screw you, Rallo!

12:23.243 --> 12:24.242
Yeah, I'll take seven.

12:30.282 --> 12:32.917
Oh, look, there's cheese stuck
to the top of the box,

12:32.919 --> 12:35.854
cooling and congealing,
turning into cheese gum.

12:35.856 --> 12:37.689
Gee, who's
gonna eat that?

12:37.691 --> 12:40.191
I'll take it!
(sighs)

12:41.127 --> 12:42.360
Thanks, bros.

12:42.362 --> 12:43.795
Pizza-pizza!

12:43.797 --> 12:46.131
So, you're really
quitting the Scouts?

12:46.133 --> 12:47.232
I thought that was,
like, you know,

12:47.234 --> 12:49.634
the most important
thing in your life.

12:49.636 --> 12:51.469
A lot of stupid crap was
important to me

12:51.471 --> 12:53.872
before I woke up.
Thanks for opening my eyes

12:53.874 --> 12:55.874
to what the world's
really like, Rallo.

12:55.876 --> 12:58.109
Well, I gotta admit,
it's nice to finally have

12:58.111 --> 13:01.246
